<parameter name="content"># Finance Manager Dashboard Structure Plan

## Overview
This document outlines the plan to create separate files for each button/page in the Finance Manager Dashboard sidebar.

## Current Sidebar Structure (to be determined)
Need to identify the sidebar buttons from FinanceManagerDashboard.jsx

## Proposed File Structure

```
src/components/dashboard/finance-manager/
├── FinanceManagerDashboard.jsx    # Main dashboard with sidebar navigation
├── pages/
│   ├── Overview.jsx              # Dashboard overview/home page
│   ├── Invoices.jsx              # Invoice management
│   ├── Expenses.jsx              # Expense tracking
│   ├── Reports.jsx               # Financial reports
│   ├── Settings.jsx              # Finance settings
│   └── Payroll.jsx               # Payroll management (if applicable)
└── components/
    ├── Sidebar.jsx               # Reusable sidebar component
    ├── Header.jsx                # Dashboard header
    └── StatsCard.jsx             # Reusable stats card component
```

## Implementation Steps

1. Create the directory structure
2. Create each page component
3. Update FinanceManagerDashboard.jsx to use the new file structure
4. Add proper routing/navigation between pages

## Notes
- Each page should be self-contained with its own styles
- Use shared components where possible to avoid duplication
- Ensure consistent layout across all pages
</parameter>
